The 2019 MyBroadband Conference and Expo will take place on 17 October at the Gallagher Convention Centre and is the one event which every ICT executive should attend. The annual MyBroadband Conference is the premier ICT event in South Africa and the meeting place for the country’s IT and telecoms community. This year, delegates will hear from South Africa’s top telecoms CEOs, including MTN SA CEO Godfrey Motsa, Liquid Telecom CEO Reshaad Sha, and Supersonic MD Calvin Collett. They will also be treated to presentations from Vodacom chief officer Jorge Mendes, SqwidNet MD Phathizwe Malinga, Q-KON Africa CEO Dawie de Wet, and Vodacom executive Jannie van Zyl. Delegates will also get the opportunity to interact with South Africa’s top telecommunications and IT companies and enjoy special deals from the conference exhibitors. Registrations for the 2019 MyBroadband Conference are open, with a big special on early-bird tickets. The tickets cover all aspects of the event, including access to the expo and conference, lunch, and refreshments.